			<ns0:name>kschi...@google.com</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/108470876877739532758/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">&lt;b&gt;[Please summarize the enhancement so it will be comprehensible to someone&lt;/b&gt;
&lt;b&gt;from outside the Native Client team. A good summary will include:]&lt;/b&gt;

&lt;b&gt;- Where are we today?&lt;/b&gt;
ncval allows defining block alignment as either 16/32, and only for the contexts where ncval calls NaClRunValidator.

&lt;b&gt;- Why is this a problem?&lt;/b&gt;
(1) Many command line options to ncval do not go through NaClRunValidator.
(2) The current command line option only allows 16 or 32, not other small values.

&lt;b&gt;- The proposed enhancement:&lt;/b&gt;
Generalize the --alignment command line argument to work for all uses of ncval, and allow any small number.

&lt;b&gt;- Exit criteria:&lt;/b&gt;
When all paths in main use the value of the --alignment argument to define the alignment value to use.

&lt;b&gt;- Anticipated impact:&lt;/b&gt;
&lt;b&gt;[for users as well as other parts of the system]&lt;/b&gt;
